SIMPLE: transatlantic
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Transatlantic
<hw>Trans`at*lan"tic</hw> <pr>(tr⟦acr⟧ns*⟦acr⟧t*l⟦acr⟧n"t⟦icr⟧k)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref. <ets>trans-</ets> + <ets>Atlantic</ets>: cf.
F. <ets>transatlantique</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Lying or being
beyond the Atlantic Ocean.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ When used by a person in Europe or Africa,
<ex>transatlantic</ex> signifies being in America; when by a person in
America, it denotes being or lying in Europe or Africa, especially the
former.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Crossing the Atlantic Ocean; <as>as, a
<ex>transatlantic</ex> flight</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Transaudient</ent>⟦br⟧
